Moreover, any non-maximal Clifford algebra is obtained from a
given maximal Clifford algebra by deleting a certain number of
Gamma matrices (as an example, Clifford algebras in
even-dimensional spacetimes are always non-maximal). It is
immediately clear from the above construction that the maximal
Clifford algebras are encountered if and only if the condition
 
is matched. The notion of Clifford's algebra of Weyl type,
