An application of the octonionic spinors. The octonionic
-algebra and the generalized supersymmetries. 

We shortly review here what is perhaps the most promising
application of the octonionic spinors, i.e. their connection with the
octonionic -algebra (and superconformal  algebra, see
), a specific example of a generalized
octonionic supersymmetry. The identities for antisymmetric
octonionic tensors play in this case a special role.The
generalized space-time supersymmetries are the ones going beyond
the standard HLS scheme. This implies that the
bosonic sector of the Poincare or conformal superalgebra no
longer can be expressed as the tensor product structure
, where  describes space-time
Poincare or conformal algebras and the remaining generators
spanning  are Lorentz-scalars.In the particular case
of the Minkowskian  dimensions, where the -theory should
be found, the following construction is allowed. The spinors are
real and have  components.As recalled in section 2 ,
by taking the anticommutator of two such spinors the most general
expected result consists of a  symmetric matrix with
 components. On the other hand, the
standard supertranslation algebra underlining the maximal
supergravity contains only the  bosonic Poincare generators
and by no means the r.h.s. saturates the total number of .
The extra generators that should be expected in the right hand
side are obtained by taking the totally antisymmetrized product of
 Gamma matrices (the total number of such objects is given by
the Newton binomial 


).
